        <li class='transform transition-transform hover:scale-105'>
          <strong>University Rankings:</strong> Research the global and subject-specific rankings to find reputable institutions that excel in your chosen field.
        </li>
        <li class='transform transition-transform hover:scale-105'>
          <strong>Location:</strong> Consider factors such as the cost of living, climate, and cultural environment in the country or city where the university is located.
        </li>
        <li class='transform transition-transform hover:scale-105'>
          <strong>Course Offerings:</strong> Make sure the university provides the courses and specializations that match your academic goals and interests.
        </li>
        <li class='transform transition-transform hover:scale-105'>
          <strong>Tuition and Fees:</strong> Assess the affordability of tuition fees and the availability of scholarships or financial aid.
        </li>
        <li class='transform transition-transform hover:scale-105'>
          <strong>Alumni Network:</strong> Look for strong alumni networks and connections to industries or companies that align with your career aspirations.
        </li>
      </ul>

